raw_meta_yaml:
schema_version: 1

context:
  name: supervisor
  version: 4.3.0

package:
  name: ${{ name|lower }}
  version: ${{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.org/packages/source/${{ name[0] }}/${{ name }}/${{ name }}-${{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 4a2bf149adf42997e1bb44b70c43b613275ec9852c3edacca86a9166b27e945e

build:
  number: 0
  skip: win

requirements:
  build:
    - if: build_platform != target_platform
      then: python
    - if: build_platform != target_platform
      then: cross-python_${{ target_platform }}
    - sed
  host:
    - python
    - setuptools
  run:
    - python
    - setuptools

tests:
  - python:
      imports:
        - supervisor
  - files:
      source:
        - supervisor/tests/
    requirements:
      run:
        - pytest >=2.5.2
        - mock >=0.5.0
        - pip
    script:
      - cp -r supervisor/tests $(python -c 'import site; print(site.getsitepackages()[0])')/supervisor
      - py.test supervisor/tests
      - supervisord -h
      - supervisorctl -h
      - echo_supervisord_conf -h
      - pip check

about:
  license: BSD-3-Clause-Modification AND BSD-3-Clause AND PSF-2.0
  license_file: LICENSES.txt
  summary: A Process Control System
  description: |
    Supervisor is a client/server system that allows its users to monitor and
    control a number of processes on UNIX-like operating systems.
  homepage: http://supervisord.org/
  repository: https://github.com/Supervisor/supervisor
  documentation: http://supervisord.org/

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - kalefranz
    - sodre
    - xhochy
